      "content": "Nausea and shaking hands are common side effects when starting lithium, especially during the initial adjustment phase. These symptoms typically resolve on their own within a few weeks as your body adapts to the medication. However, if the symptoms persist or worsen, it's possible that you need to adjust your dosage or monitor your medication levels. I recommend speaking with your doctor to discuss your symptoms and determine the best course of action.",
